post_text:
WE'VE GONE PAPERLESS!

We need all student information updated by September 20, 2020. Information and passwords were included in your back to school mailing.

If you do NOT have a PowerSchool account follow the link below to create one. One account is needed per family. All family members can be linked to the same account after it has been created.

After creating your account and signing in go to 'Forms' on the left side to fill out all needed documents.

https://ps.braham.k12.mn.us/public/create_multi_student_account.html?

If you HAVE an account follow the link below, sign in and go to 'Forms' on the left side of the page to fill out needed documents.

https://ps.braham.k12.mn.us/public/

This information will help us keep you updated on your child's progress, grades, attendance and school emergency information.
We appreciate your help. Happy school year!!

Congratulations on earning a 2020 Presidential Academic Award. This is quite an honor! Please know that I am extremely proud of you. Normally we would have handed these out at a ceremony at the end of the school year. Due to distance learning, we were unable to do this. You will be receiving a certificate when we return to school and recognition at that time.

The linked video below explains in greater detail the award you earned and the criteria.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=67OvRODHRJM

Congratulations again! I'm very excited for the opportunity we have to come back to school this fall. I look forward to seeing many of you then!

Stay safe and enjoy the rest of your summer!

Enjoy working with children??

Braham Area Schools has an opening for a BASK Coordinator.

BASK is a before and after school kids care program available to elementary aged students with care provided from 6:30 a.m. until school starts, and after school until 6:00 p.m.

BASK Coordinator schedule follows the school calendar for student contact days: 6:15 a.m. - 8:00 a.m.
2:45 p.m. - 6:00 p.m.

Please visit our school webpage http:/www.braham.k12.mn.us to apply, please call 320-396-5180 for any questions

post_text:
Attention all Braham students in grades 7-12 (fall of 2020):

Interested in a summer workout? You have been emailed a summer workout program which does include four attached documents:
Summer Weight Training for Braham Students (calendar of workouts)
Braham Summer Training (with clickable links for demonstration purposes)
Agility Drills
Dynamic Warmup
This training program is designed for use three times a week and includes some weight training designed specifically to work each part of your body, some agility drills as well as some sprinting drills.

Since we are not able to be in the school building just yet, we hope that this will give you the opportunity to do a summer workout program. Whether you are doing to stay in shape for an after-school activity, doing it to just stay in shape, or just for fun, we hope you enjoy this equipment free workout!

We are pleased to announce that the Frandsen Family Scholarship has been extended to our 2021 Seniors. This scholarship allows students to attend Pine Technical and Community College COMPLETELY FREE for 2 years, as well as provides a $1000 stipend for books and/or supplies. Additional information will be presented during the 2020-2021 school year. Please feel free to contact Amanda Tessmer with questions in the meantime!

A huge THANK YOU to the Frandsen Family Foundation for their generous offer and continued support of our students!!

post_text:
The week of January 27  31, 2020, is Paraprofessional Recognition Week. We would like to say a special thank you to all our paraprofessionals at both the elementary & high school buildings!

Paraprofessionals can and do wear numerous hats throughout the school day. They work with students with special needs in a small group or one-on-one situations, they assist the classroom teachers with ensuring the needs of the students are met, they supervise the playground during recess, they monitor the cafeteria, they help run the media center, assist in the library, etc. This list could go on and on. One thing is certain; they are necessary for our students and teachers to help ensure learning success. They are also essential to the smooth operation of a school. We certainly do appreciate the work they do, and they support the student population that needs more help to be successful in school. Speaking on behalf of the administration, we are very fortunate to have a talented group that really cares about students. Thats a combination you look for, no matter who works in your school.

One thing is certain; they are necessary for our students and teachers to help ensure learning success. They are also essential to the smooth operation of a school. We certainly do appreciate the work they do, and they support the student population that needs more help to be successful in school. Speaking on behalf of the administration, we are very fortunate to have a talented group that really cares about students. Thats a combination you look for, no matter who works in your school.

Annual Mitten Tree & Food Drive

The Braham Elementary School will be collecting new mittens, gloves, scarves, and hats for our mitten tree. In addition to the mitten tree, we are collecting non-perishable food items. The collection will begin on Monday, December 2nd and end on Thursday, December 19th
